        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 22 at 12:30AM CDT until August 22 at 1:15AM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 1230 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles northeast
of Ree Heights, or 9 miles northwest of Miller, moving east at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Two inch hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Ree Heights.
</description>
        <instruction>Prepare immediately for large hail and deadly cloud to ground
lightning. Seek shelter inside a well-built structure. Stay away from
windows.

To report severe weather contact your nearest law enforcement agency.
They will send your report to the National Weather Service office in
Aberdeen.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
